Beef Rump (800g-1kg) [HALAL]
description:
Country of origin: India.

This is a frozen item.
The rump is a boneless five-muscled primal that sits between the sirloin and topside. Rump steak is made up of four of these muscles with differing tenderness. It is a very full-flavoured piece of meat that is excellent and versatile when roasted, braised or casseroled, stir fried or pan fried. As it is taken from a working muscle, rump steaks, or the whole rump joint may be a little tough, but they are full of flavour.

Slice thinly, and you will turn it into what is known as Minute Steaks, which is very good for cooking on the barbeque.

Please allow 7% to 10% weight fluctuation due to cutting, trimming and packaging.

All images are for illustration purposes only. Actual product may vary due to product packaging and presentation.

name: Beef Neck Bone (800g-1kg) [HALAL]
description:
Country of origin: India.

This is a frozen item.

The neck bone is just as tender though somewhat less fatty than oxtail. Due to the tendons and bones found in the neck, it can be a rather tough cut if cooked quickly, but if braised or stewed low and slow, the meat around the bone will become tender.

Please allow 7% to 10% weight fluctuation due to cutting, trimming and packaging.

Sweet Potato (Japanese) / 日本番薯 +/-500g
description: Japanese sweet potatoes have a deep pinkish purple skin and whitish flesh that turns golden when baked. It is sweeter than normal sweet potato. Best steamed or baked whole with skin on and served piping hot. They do not require any seasoning and are deliciously sweet and fibreless.
additionalInfoDescription1:
Store the sweet potato in a dry and cool area. An area like the pantry. Not the refrigerator as that will encourage sprouting. Do not wash the potato before storing as moisture left on the potato could lead to rotting. Instead, clean any dirt with a dry cloth.

Do not store the potato near other vegetables as it could cause others to ripen more quickly than preferred. Keep the potato in a paper bag or a basket.
